dotfiles
========

my configuration files


installation
------------

installation is done using GNU stow[1]

 $ git clone --recurse-submodules git@github.com:424ever/dotfiles.git ~/dotfiles
 $ cd ~/dotfiles
 $ ./install           # install everything
 $ stow git            # install only git configuration


dependencies
------------

some configuration expects software to be installed on your system

bat/
  bat[2]
  bat-extras[11]

  shell/

eza/
  eza[7]

  shell/

ghostty/
  ghostty[12]

git/
  git[3]
  delta[4]

lazygit/
  git[3]
  lazygit[5]

  git/

ripgrep/
  ripgrep[8]

  shell/

shell/
  fish[6]

tmux/
  tmux[9]

  shell/

zoxide/
  zoxide[10]

  shell/


notes
-----

some maybe unexpected things

 - installing git/ creates `~/.config/git/config`. you can add configuration
   like `user.name` and `user.email` in your `~/.gitconfig`
 - installing bat/, eza/, lazygit/, ripgrep/, tmux/, or zoxide/ creates shell
   configuration in `~/.config/fish/conf.d`
 - installing tmux/ means that tmux will automatically start with fish

